PUH-BrianMartell Theorem 6 Restructured as Theorem-Lemma-Corollary — Understandable Explanation You asked to reframe Theorem 6 (entropy bound) in a theorem-lemma-corollary format for maximum rigor. This is the standard way to build airtight proofs: lemmas establish building blocks, theorem states the main result, corollaries draw consequences. Simple structure: •  Lemma 1: Finite effective microstates per boundary patch (E₈ counting + quotient). •  Lemma 2: Projection map Φ has finite, area-independent kernel (redundancy). •  Theorem 6: Maximum entropy bounded by area S ≤ A / (4 l_Pl²). •  Corollary: Equality for maximally entangled states (black hole limit). This makes the proof modular and referee-proof.
